Binding Site Analysis of 1B6A using PyMOL
=========================================
A Complete, Annotated, and Reproducible Workflow
This document describes how to:
- Load and visualize the protein–ligand complex (PDB ID 1B6A) in PyMOL
- Select ligands and annotated binding site residues
- Generate two publication-quality snapshots
- Identify the six extreme (opposite) residues based on coordinate extrema
- Compute binding site residues using two independent methods (annotated + computational)
------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1 — Load the Molecule in PyMOL
-----------------------------------
GUI Method:
1. Open PyMOL
2. Go to: File → Open…
3. Select 1B6A.pdb
Command:
load 1B6A.pdb
------------------------------------------------------------
Step 2 — Select Ligands and Binding Site
----------------------------------------Select Ligands (TN4 + CO):
select main_ligands, resn TN4 or resn CO
Select Binding Site (from SITE record):
select site_ac3, resi 231+327+328+329+331+338+339+364+444
------------------------------------------------------------
Step 3 — Snapshot 1: Full Binding Site Visualization
----------------------------------------------------
Prepare Scene:
bg_color white
hide all
show cartoon
Show Ligands and Binding Site:
show sticks, main_ligands
color byelement, main_ligands
show sticks, site_ac3
Save Snapshot:
zoom site_ac3, 8
png snapshot_1_full_site.png
------------------------------------------------------------
Step 4 — Six Extreme Residues (Coordinate Extremes)
----------------------------------------------------
X-Axis:- Min: HIS 331
- Max: HIS 231
Y-Axis:
- Min: GLU 364
- Max: TYR 444
Z-Axis:
- Min: ILE 338
- Max: ASN 327
Final 6 extreme residues:
- HIS 231
- HIS 331
- GLU 364
- TYR 444
- ILE 338
- ASN 327
------------------------------------------------------------
Step 5 — Snapshot 2: Extreme Residue Visualization
---------------------------------------------------
Selection:
select extremes, resi 231+331+364+444+338+327
Visualization:
hide sticks, site_ac3
show ball_and_stick, extremeslabel n. CA and extremes, "%s %s" % (resn, resi)
Save Snapshot:
zoom extremes, 12
png snapshot_2_extreme_residues.png
------------------------------------------------------------
Method 1 — Annotated Binding Site (PDB SITE Record)
----------------------------------------------------
SITE entries in 1B6A define residues:
HIS 231, ASN 327, LEU 328, ASN 329,
HIS 331, ILE 338, HIS 339, GLU 364, TYR 444
------------------------------------------------------------
Method 2 — Computational Binding Site (Distance Method)
--------------------------------------------------------
Identify Ligand:
select ligand, organic
Compute Binding Site:
select binding_site, byres polymer within 5 of ligand
Visualization:
hide sticks, all
show cartoon
show sticks, binding_site
show sticks, ligandzoom binding_site, 8
